parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle pulls to one side
the power steering fails intermittently
the steering wheel locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights randomly illuminate
the brake lights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or refuse to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle loses power
the engine RPMs fluctuate
the vehicle is unable to reverse or accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can increase the risk of rear-end collisions, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The brake lights stay on or off
the brake lights flicker or flash
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle's electronic stability control (ESC) and traction control systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
